"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebsite_new=self.webpackChunkwebsite_new||[]).push([[4392],{16901(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"rayforge-1.8-rust-pipeline-faster-rasterizing-grbl-simple","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.8-rust-pipeline-faster-rasterizing-grbl-simple","source":"@site/blog/2026-06-09-rayforge-1.8-rust-pipeline-faster-rasterizing-grbl-simple.md","title":"Rayforge 1.8 Beta - Rust-Powered Pipeline, Faster Rasterizing, New GRBL Driver","description":"Rayforge 1.8 beta rewrites the core pipeline in Rust, redesigns the Ops data structure, ports raster and image processing to Rust, adds a simple GRBL serial driver, and includes new device profiles.","date":"2026-06-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.8","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-8"},{"inline":true,"label":"rust","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/rust"},{"inline":true,"label":"raygeo","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/raygeo"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/performance"},{"inline":true,"label":"grbl","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/grbl"},{"inline":true,"label":"raster","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/raster"},{"inline":true,"label":"ops","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/ops"}],"readingTime":2.9,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.8-rust-pipeline-faster-rasterizing-grbl-simple","title":"Rayforge 1.8 Beta - Rust-Powered Pipeline, Faster Rasterizing, New GRBL Driver","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.8","rust","raygeo","performance","grbl","raster","ops"],"description":"Rayforge 1.8 beta rewrites the core pipeline in Rust, redesigns the Ops data structure, ports raster and image processing to Rust, adds a simple GRBL serial driver, and includes new device profiles."},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 - CO2/Fiber Lasers, Ruida, OctoPrint, Config Wizard","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.8 beta brings a Rust-powered geometry pipeline, a completely\\nredesigned Ops data structure, raster and image processing ported to Rust, a\\nnew simple GRBL serial driver, and new device profiles.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Ops Redesigned with Struct-of-Arrays\\n\\nThe core Ops container has been completely rewritten from a list of Python\\nCommand objects to a **Struct-of-Arrays** layout with index-based access.\\nThis new design is significantly faster in Python and serves as the\\nfoundation for the Rust backend integration. Every transformer, encoder,\\nproducer, and the 3D simulator has been ported to the new API.\\n\\n## Geometry Processing in Rust (raygeo 0.6)\\n\\nFive major pipeline stages now run entirely in Rust via raygeo 0.6: **tab\\noperations**, **merge lines**, **overscan**, **lead-in/lead-out**, and **hull\\ncomputation**. Each has been rewritten as a thin Python wrapper around\\nraygeo\'s Rust functions, and the old Python implementations have been\\nremoved. This is the continuation of the migration that started in 1.7.8.\\n\\n## Raster Engine in Rust\\n\\nRaster scan loops -- the hot path for engraving operations -- have been\\nreplaced with Rust-accelerated raygeo functions for power modulation, mask\\nscanning, and multi-pass modes. Auto-level computation and grayscale\\nnormalization also run in Rust. All 39 existing raster tests pass unchanged.\\n\\n## Image Processing in Rust\\n\\nsRGB-to-linear conversion, linear-to-sRGB, all dithering algorithms\\n(Floyd-Steinberg, Bayer, minimum run length), auto-level computation, and\\ngrayscale normalization are now handled by raygeo.image. The Python side\\nkeeps only thin Cairo surface buffer wrappers.\\n\\n## 3D Canvas Slider Performance\\n\\nThe 3D playback scrubber now pre-computes snapshots every 1000 commands at\\nload time and uses binary search during playback. For a 338K-command job,\\nseek time drops from seconds to roughly 3 milliseconds.\\n\\n## Simple GRBL Serial Driver (Experimental)\\n\\nA new **GrblSerialSimpleDriver** uses a ping-pong protocol: send one line,\\nwait for \\"ok\\", send the next. No character-counting buffer management, no\\ndeadlock detection, no stall recovery. Useful for devices where the advanced\\nbuffer-counting driver causes false alarms or communication errors.\\n\\n## Adaptive Deadlock Timeouts\\n\\nThe GRBL driver now estimates per-command execution time and sets individual\\ntimeouts accordingly. Slow moves get longer timeouts, fast moves get shorter\\nones. This eliminates false ALARM:3 errors on slow feed rates.\\n\\n## Go to WCS Zero\\n\\nA new button in the Current Position section moves the machine to X0 Y0 of\\nthe active Work Coordinate System.\\n\\n## New Device Profiles\\n\\n- **Creality Falcon 10W** -- 10W diode laser with 400x415mm work area\\n- **Sculpfun C1** -- diode laser engraver\\n\\n## Finer Raster Line Spacing\\n\\nThe minimum raster line spacing has been lowered from 0.01 mm to 0.001 mm\\nwith 3-digit decimal precision, enabling sub-10 micron pitch work for\\nmicrofabrication and precision lithography.\\n\\n## Machine Settings Apply Immediately\\n\\nMachine settings changes now propagate to the pipeline and canvas without\\nrequiring a restart. Driver, dialect, laser, and axis changes are all picked\\nup live.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- Worker pool detects crashed and unresponsive workers, spawns replacements\\n  automatically\\n- Fixed GRBL network disconnect with MKS DLC32 boards\\n- Fixed ValueError when removing the active machine\\n- Fixed manual laser control routing\\n- File dialogs now prefer Rayforge project and sketch MIME types\\n- Deadlock detection can now be toggled on/off per driver\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nfroqstar, old-man-and-the-seam, pghpete, Derek McTavish, starlynx.dev, and\\nfive anonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.8 Beta\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-04-rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard.md","title":"Rayforge 1.7 - CO2/Fiber Lasers, Ruida, OctoPrint, Config Wizard","description":"Rayforge 1.7 brings CO2 and fiber laser support, a Ruida driver, OctoPrint integration, a configuration wizard, job sanity checks, and 15 new device profiles.","date":"2026-05-04T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.7","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-7"},{"inline":true,"label":"co2","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/co-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"fiber","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/fiber"},{"inline":true,"label":"ruida","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/ruida"},{"inline":true,"label":"octoprint","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/octoprint"},{"inline":true,"label":"pwm","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/pwm"},{"inline":true,"label":"config-wizard","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/config-wizard"},{"inline":true,"label":"sanity-checks","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sanity-checks"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sketcher"}],"readingTime":4.91,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard","title":"Rayforge 1.7 - CO2/Fiber Lasers, Ruida, OctoPrint, Config Wizard","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.7","co2","fiber","ruida","octoprint","pwm","config-wizard","sanity-checks","sketcher"],"description":"Rayforge 1.7 brings CO2 and fiber laser support, a Ruida driver, OctoPrint integration, a configuration wizard, job sanity checks, and 15 new device profiles."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.8 Beta - Rust-Powered Pipeline, Faster Rasterizing, New GRBL Driver","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.8-rust-pipeline-faster-rasterizing-grbl-simple"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta 2 - Job Sanity Checks, 10 New Device Profiles, Better Layers","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.7 brings CO2 and fiber laser support, a Ruida driver, an\\nexperimental OctoPrint driver, a configuration wizard for GRBL devices, job\\nsanity checks, a manual laser control dock, parametric text templates, and 15\\nnew device profiles.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## CO2 and Fiber Laser PWM Settings\\n\\nRayforge now understands that not all lasers are diodes. A new **Laser Type**\\ndropdown in the laser head settings lets you choose between Diode, CO2, and\\nFiber. When you select CO2 or Fiber, a dedicated PWM section appears with\\ncontrols for frequency and pulse width -- including configurable min/max bounds.\\n\\nThese settings flow through the pipeline, so each operation step can use or\\noverride the defaults. The Ruida driver already leverages them for native\\nfrequency and pulse width commands.\\n\\n## Ruida Driver\\n\\nA complete **Ruida driver** is now available with jogging, position reporting,\\nair assist, layer selection, auto-connect, status polling, and reference\\npoints support. It has been tested with a real controller.\\n\\nGeneric device profiles for Ruida, GRBL, and Smoothieware are included so you\\ncan get started even without a machine-specific profile.\\n\\n## Configuration Wizard\\n\\nSetting up a new machine is now much easier. The new **configuration wizard**\\nprobes GRBL devices over serial or network, detects the firmware version and\\nsettings, and creates a machine profile automatically. Just plug in your\\ncontroller, pick the driver, and let the wizard handle the rest.\\n\\n## OctoPrint Driver (Experimental)\\n\\nA new driver lets you submit G-code directly to an **OctoPrint** server over\\nthe network. It connects via WebSocket for real-time status updates and falls\\nback to REST polling when needed. Setup requires just a hostname and API key,\\nand the driver includes a \\"Request Access\\" flow that walks you through\\nOctoPrint\'s application key system.\\n\\nThis driver is labeled experimental and has not been tested on real hardware\\nyet. If you have an OctoPrint setup, your feedback would be invaluable.\\n\\n## Manual Laser Control Dock\\n\\nA new dockable panel gives you hands-on laser control with per-head power,\\nfrequency, pulse width, and an auto-off timer. Useful for testing, alignment,\\nand manual positioning.\\n\\n## Job Sanity Checks\\n\\nBefore sending or exporting a job, Rayforge now runs a set of composable\\nsanity checks and presents the results in a structured dialog. The system\\ncatches three categories of problems:\\n\\n- **Machine extent violations** -- geometry extending beyond what your machine\\n  can physically reach\\n- **Workarea violations** -- workpieces outside the configured workarea\\n  boundaries\\n- **No-go zone collisions** -- geometry overlapping restricted areas defined\\n  in machine settings\\n\\nEach check produces at most one issue per unique violation, keeping the\\ndialog readable even for complex projects.\\n\\n## Parametric Text Templates\\n\\nText boxes in the sketcher now support template expressions using curly braces.\\nAny sketch parameter or input variable can be referenced:\\n\\n- `{width}` resolves to the current width value\\n- `{name}` resolves to a string input parameter\\n- `{sqrt(area):.1f}` evaluates math and formats the result\\n\\nBuilt-in functions include `{today()}` for the current date, `{now()}` for a\\nfull timestamp, and `{uuid4()}` for a unique 8-character identifier.\\n\\nText rendering has also been improved: Now Pango is used internally, which\\ndraws text more accurately than the old Cairo-based rendering.\\n\\n## 15 New Device Profiles\\n\\nOut-of-the-box support for popular laser cutters:\\n\\n- **Ortur** Laser Master 3 and Laser Master 4\\n- **Atomstack** X40 Pro and A70\\n- **TwoTrees** TTS-55\\n- **NEJE** Master 3 Max\\n- **Creality** Falcon 2 Pro\\n- **OMTech** Polar 50W\\n- **Longer** Ray5\\n- **Thunder Laser** Nova 35\\n- **Sculpfun** iCube Ultra, S30 Pro Max, S40 MAX, and S70 MAX\\n- **Elidor** Z6\\n\\n## Better Layer Interaction\\n\\nLayer columns now highlight selected workpieces and stay in sync with the\\ncanvas selection:\\n\\n- **Single click** selects one item\\n- **Ctrl-click** toggles individual items in a multi-selection\\n- **Shift-click** selects a range within a column\\n- **Drag** moves selected items between layers, including across multiple\\n  layers at once\\n\\nRight-clicking a workpiece in the layer tab opens a context menu with move,\\ndelete, and properties actions. The asset browser also received context menus\\nwith copy, cut, paste, and duplicate operations.\\n\\n## Direct Vector Editing\\n\\nYou can now double-click a workpiece to edit its vectors directly -- delete\\nindividual paths without having to go back to an external editor. This is a\\nfirst step toward fuller in-app vector editing.\\n\\n## Linear Light Image Processing\\n\\nAll image processing -- resizing, grayscale conversion, dithering, and color\\nLUT gradients -- now operates in linear light instead of sRGB. This produces\\nmore accurate interpolation when scaling and better dithering quality,\\nespecially for gradients and fine detail.\\n\\n## Sketcher Auto-Constraints\\n\\nThe path tool now automatically creates horizontal and vertical constraints\\nwhen the snap engine shows alignment guides during drawing. Your geometry\\ncomes out more precise with less manual constraint management.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Job time estimate** shown in the 3D canvas\\n- **Search field** in the machine profile selector\\n- **Sketch parameters** displayed as a separate preferences group\\n- **Locale-aware number formatting** in sliders\\n- **Grid toggle** in the 3D canvas visibility overlay\\n- **Debug log** can optionally include the project file\\n- **Project files** are now zipped internally\\n- **GRBL serial transport** -- non-blocking read, offloaded writes, exclusive\\n  port mode, buffer flushing, and multiple deadlock fixes\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nFixed GRBL buffer overflow on devices with smaller RX buffers, GRBL buffer\\ndeadlock from lost ok responses on certain line endings, laser-off command\\nsent during active jog causing error:9, deadlock detection false positives,\\nparametric text not updating with volatile expressions, crash in\\nMergeLinesTransformer, wrong visibility icon for invisible layers, IndexError\\nand AttributeError on startup, circle and ellipse sketches missing thumbnails,\\ncanvas stuck in shift-pressed state, pipeline holding stale machine\\nreferences, pipeline recalculation loop, power percentage rounding in step\\nsummaries, and many more stability fixes.\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nAmsel, froqstar, old-man-and-the-seam, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.7\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-02-rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers.md","title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta 2 - Job Sanity Checks, 10 New Device Profiles, Better Layers","description":"Rayforge 1.7 beta 2 adds job sanity checks, 10 new device profiles, improved layer interaction with multi-selection and context menus, and sketcher auto-constraints.","date":"2026-05-02T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.7","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-7"},{"inline":true,"label":"sanity-checks","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sanity-checks"},{"inline":true,"label":"device-profiles","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/device-profiles"},{"inline":true,"label":"layers","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/layers"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sketcher"}],"readingTime":2.57,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers","title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta 2 - Job Sanity Checks, 10 New Device Profiles, Better Layers","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.7","sanity-checks","device-profiles","layers","sketcher"],"description":"Rayforge 1.7 beta 2 adds job sanity checks, 10 new device profiles, improved layer interaction with multi-selection and context menus, and sketcher auto-constraints."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 - CO2/Fiber Lasers, Ruida, OctoPrint, Config Wizard","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-lasers-ruida-octoprint-config-wizard"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta - CO2 Laser Support, OctoPrint, Parametric Text","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.7 beta 2 brings a new safety net for your jobs, profiles for ten\\nmore popular laser cutters, and a significantly improved layer interaction\\nexperience.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Job Sanity Checks\\n\\nBefore sending or exporting a job, Rayforge now runs a set of composable\\nsanity checks and presents the results in a structured dialog. The system\\ncatches three categories of problems:\\n\\n- **Machine extent violations** -- geometry extending beyond what your machine\\n  can physically reach, reported per axis and direction\\n- **Workarea violations** -- workpieces outside the configured workarea\\n  boundaries\\n- **No-go zone collisions** -- geometry overlapping restricted areas defined\\n  in machine settings\\n\\nEach check produces at most one issue per unique violation, keeping the\\ndialog readable even for complex projects. Errors and warnings are clearly\\nseparated so you can make an informed decision before proceeding.\\n\\n## 10 New Device Profiles\\n\\nThis release adds out-of-the-box support for some of the most popular laser\\ncutters in the community:\\n\\n- **Ortur** Laser Master 3 and Laser Master 4\\n- **Atomstack** X40 Pro and A70\\n- **TwoTrees** TTS-55\\n- **NEJE** Master 3 Max\\n- **Creality** Falcon 2 Pro\\n- **OMTech** Polar 50W\\n- **Longer** Ray5\\n- **Thunder Laser** Nova 35\\n\\nGRBL-based devices in this batch use the raster dialect for cleaner G-code\\noutput. If your machine isn\'t listed yet, open an issue on GitHub and we\'ll\\nget it added.\\n\\n## Better Layer Interaction\\n\\nLayer columns now highlight selected workpieces and stay in sync with the\\ncanvas selection. This makes it much easier to see what you\'re working with:\\n\\n- **Single click** selects one item\\n- **Ctrl-click** toggles individual items in a multi-selection\\n- **Shift-click** selects a range within a column\\n- **Drag** moves selected items between layers, including across multiple\\n  layers at once\\n\\nRight-clicking a workpiece in the layer tab opens a context menu with move,\\ndelete, and properties actions. The asset browser also received context menus\\nwith copy, cut, paste, and duplicate operations.\\n\\n## Sketcher Auto-Constraints\\n\\nThe path tool now automatically creates horizontal and vertical constraints\\nwhen the snap engine shows alignment guides during drawing. Your geometry\\ncomes out more precise with less manual constraint management. This also\\nfixes a bug where snap-derived constraints could reference wrong point IDs\\nand cause solver failures.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Sketch parameters** displayed as a separate preferences group in the\\n  properties panel\\n- **Locale-aware number formatting** in sliders (proper decimal separators)\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\n- Fixed GRBL buffer deadlock from lost ok responses on \\\\r\\\\r\\\\n line endings\\n- Fixed wrong visibility icon for initially invisible layers\\n- Fixed IndexError when laser combo selection is out of sync with machine\\n  heads\\n- Fixed AttributeError on startup from early view_stack signal connection\\n- Fixed circle and ellipse sketches missing preview thumbnails\\n- Fixed canvas stuck in shift-pressed state after layer interaction\\n- Fixed incorrect 3D view mouse controls in the documentation (#229)\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nAmsel, froqstar, old-man-and-the-seam, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.7 Beta 2\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-01-rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text.md","title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta - CO2 Laser Support, OctoPrint, Parametric Text","description":"Rayforge 1.7 beta brings CO2 and fiber laser PWM settings, an experimental OctoPrint driver, parametric text templates in the sketcher, and linear light image processing.","date":"2026-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.7","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-7"},{"inline":true,"label":"co2","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/co-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"octoprint","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/octoprint"},{"inline":true,"label":"pwm","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/pwm"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sketcher"},{"inline":true,"label":"image-processing","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/image-processing"}],"readingTime":2.33,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text","title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta - CO2 Laser Support, OctoPrint, Parametric Text","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.7","co2","octoprint","pwm","sketcher","image-processing"],"description":"Rayforge 1.7 beta brings CO2 and fiber laser PWM settings, an experimental OctoPrint driver, parametric text templates in the sketcher, and linear light image processing."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta 2 - Job Sanity Checks, 10 New Device Profiles, Better Layers","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-beta2-sanity-checks-device-profiles-layers"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.7 beta expands hardware support to CO2 and fiber lasers, adds an\\nexperimental OctoPrint driver, brings template expressions to the sketcher text\\ntool, and improves image processing accuracy across the board.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## CO2 and Fiber Laser PWM Settings\\n\\nRayforge now understands that not all lasers are diodes. A new **Laser Type**\\ndropdown in the laser head settings lets you choose between Diode, CO2, and\\nFiber. When you select CO2 or Fiber, a dedicated PWM section appears with\\ncontrols for frequency and pulse width -- including configurable min/max bounds.\\n\\nThese settings flow through the pipeline, so each operation step can use or\\noverride the defaults. The Ruida driver already leverages them for native\\nfrequency and pulse width commands.\\n\\n## OctoPrint Driver (Experimental)\\n\\nA new driver lets you submit G-code directly to an OctoPrint server over the\\nnetwork. It connects via WebSocket for real-time status updates and falls back\\nto REST polling when needed. Setup requires just a hostname and an API key, and\\nthe driver includes a \\"Request Access\\" flow that walks you through OctoPrint\'s\\napplication key system.\\n\\nThis driver is labeled experimental and has not been tested on real hardware\\nyet. If you have an OctoPrint setup, your feedback would be invaluable.\\n\\n## Parametric Text Templates\\n\\nText boxes in the sketcher now support template expressions using curly braces.\\nAny sketch parameter or input variable can be referenced:\\n\\n- `{width}` resolves to the current width value\\n- `{name}` resolves to a string input parameter\\n- `{sqrt(area):.1f}` evaluates math and formats the result\\n\\nBuilt-in functions include `{today()}` for the current date, `{now()}` for a\\nfull timestamp, and `{uuid4()}` for a unique 8-character identifier. This makes\\nit easy to label parts with live dimensions, date-stamp production pieces, or\\ngenerate serial numbers.\\n\\n## Linear Light Image Processing\\n\\nAll image processing -- resizing, grayscale conversion, dithering, and color\\nLUT gradients -- now operates in linear light instead of sRGB. This produces\\nmore accurate interpolation when scaling and better dithering quality,\\nespecially for gradients and fine detail where sRGB\'s nonlinear curve used to\\ncause banding.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Sculpfun iCube Ultra** device profile added\\n- **Grid toggle** in the 3D canvas visibility overlay\\n- **Debug log** can optionally include the project file\\n- **Device profile selector** received visual improvements\\n- **Tab power slider** is now hidden for non-cut steps\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\n- Fixed GRBL buffer overflow on devices with smaller RX buffers\\n- Fixed parametric text not updating correctly with volatile expressions\\n- Fixed crash in MergeLinesTransformer when a cutting command appeared before\\n  any positioning command\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nAmsel, froqstar, old-man-and-the-seam, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.7 Beta\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-24-rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut.md","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon.","date":"2026-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.6","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-6"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"device-profiles","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/device-profiles"},{"inline":true,"label":"print-and-cut","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/print-and-cut"},{"inline":true,"label":"layers","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/layers"}],"readingTime":2.6,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.6","rotary","device-profiles","print-and-cut","layers"],"description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.7 Beta - CO2 Laser Support, OctoPrint, Parametric Text","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.7-co2-octoprint-parametric-text"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary axis overhaul, a new device profile\\nsystem, a redesigned layer system with per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon\\nfor aligning laser cuts with printed material.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Device Profiles\\n\\nMachine profiles have been replaced by **device profiles** -- declarative\\npackages that bundle your work area, axis setup, laser settings, and G-code\\ndialect into a single file. Pick your device and everything is pre-configured.\\nYou can export and import profiles to share setups between machines or back up\\nyour configuration.\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Overhaul\\n\\nRotary support was rewritten from the ground up with proper kinematics. The new\\nsystem supports a **true 4th axis** alongside your existing X, Y, and Z axes,\\nas well as **axis replacement mode** for setups where the rotary takes over X\\nor Y. Roller-type rotary attachments get their own dedicated settings.\\n\\nThe 2D canvas adapts to rotary mode automatically, and the 3D canvas renders\\nrotary toolpaths correctly in every configuration -- including during simulation\\nplayback. The kinematics engine was refactored to build dynamically from an axis\\nset and mapper, making it far more flexible and correct.\\n\\n## Print and Cut\\n\\nA new addon helps you align laser cuts with pre-printed material. Register\\nreference points on your print, let Rayforge calculate the offset and rotation,\\nand your cuts land exactly where they should. Perfect for making stickers,\\nlabels, or anything that needs to line up with an existing print.\\n\\n## Redesigned Layer System\\n\\nThe layer panel got a complete overhaul. Each layer column now shows a visual\\nworkflow so you can see your operations at a glance. You can reorder layers and\\nworkpieces with drag-and-drop. Each layer can be assigned its own Work\\nCoordinate System (G54-G59) for multi-fixture setups, with a quick edit button\\nright in the layer settings. The settings dialog is non-modal, so you can keep\\nit open while working on the canvas.\\n\\n## Material Test Grid\\n\\nNew parameter combinations are available, and multipass mode now shows extra\\nspeed or power labels so you can tell exactly what each cell represents.\\n\\n## GRBL Telnet Driver\\n\\nCommunity contributor gyordanov built a new driver that connects to GRBL\\ncontrollers over the network via Telnet. It works with grblHAL and ESP3D-based\\nboards -- no USB cable needed.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Update checker** notifies you when a new version is available\\n- **Floating properties panel** gives you more canvas space\\n- **Editable slider values** -- click and type the exact number you want\\n- **Ops color setting** -- choose layer color or laser color for rendering\\n- **Creality Falcon A1** device profile\\n- **Massively reduced memory** usage for multi-layer PDFs\\n- **GRBL serial improvements** with deadlock recovery and comment stripping\\n- **Sketcher** -- support changing text color using the fill tool\\n- **Canvas** -- right-click context menu for empty space\\n- **Windows** -- terminal window no longer appears on startup\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nold-man-and-the-seam, Amsel, froqstar, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.6\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-09-rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones.md","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains.","date":"2026-04-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.5","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-5"},{"inline":true,"label":"simulator","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/simulator"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"nogozones","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/nogozones"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/performance"}],"readingTime":3.34,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.5","simulator","bezier","nogozones","performance"],"description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native\\ncubic bezier curve support (G5), no-go zones with collision checking, and\\nsignificant performance and memory improvements.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 3D Simulator\\n\\nThe 3D canvas now has a complete job simulator. You can watch your job execute\\nstep by step -- the laser head moves along the toolpath, the beam appears when\\nthe laser fires, and bitmap engravings are progressively revealed as the\\nplayhead advances.\\n\\nPlayback controls sit at the bottom of the canvas: play/pause, step forward\\nand backward, a scrubber slider, and a speed button that cycles through 1x\\nto 16x. Rotary mode works too -- the cylinder rotates along with the\\nsimulation. All of this runs without blocking the rest of the interface, even\\non complex jobs.\\n\\n## Bezier Curves (G5)\\n\\nRayforge now supports native cubic bezier curves through the entire pipeline --\\nfrom import all the way to G-code output. For machines running LinuxCNC or\\nMarlin, curves are emitted as G5 commands instead of thousands of tiny line\\nsegments. The result is smoother cuts, smaller G-code files, and faster\\nexecution. For machines that don\'t support G5 (Grbl, Smoothieware, and\\nothers), curves are automatically linearized -- no configuration needed.\\n\\nThis touched nearly every part of the system. Tabs, cropping, smoothing,\\nmulti-pass, and path optimization all handle curves properly now.\\n\\n## No-Go Zones\\n\\nYou can now define restricted areas in your machine settings. These mark areas\\non the bed where the laser should not cut -- clamps, fixtures, or that corner\\nwhere the hose always gets in the way. Rayforge checks for collisions and warns\\nyou before sending G-code.\\n\\n## Performance and Memory\\n\\nThe canvas is significantly more responsive. When you drag, pan, or zoom,\\nexpensive laser-path rendering is suppressed until you stop moving -- no more\\nstuttering while repositioning a workpiece. Multi-step workflows render faster\\nbecause all visible steps are composited into a single surface.\\n\\nLarge images that used to cause multi-gigabyte memory spikes are now\\nautomatically scaled to sensible limits. The image handling was rewritten to\\navoid unnecessary copies, and caching is smarter -- shared images are rendered\\nonce and reused across workpieces. Two memory leaks in the 3D simulator were\\nalso fixed.\\n\\n## Dockable Bottom Panel\\n\\nThe bottom panel tabs can now be rearranged freely. Drag a tab onto the divider\\nbetween columns to split it off into its own column. You can keep the layer\\nlist and G-code viewer visible side by side, for example. The layout persists\\nbetween sessions.\\n\\n## Asset Browser\\n\\nThe asset browser has been overhauled. All assets are visible and can be\\ndragged to the canvas or to a specific layer. Multi-selection works for\\ndrag-and-drop and bulk deletion. Thumbnails are generated for most image\\nformats, and when the browser is empty it shows a helpful placeholder with\\nbuttons to add stock or a sketch.\\n\\n## New Import Options\\n\\nThe import dialog offers three layer modes: flatten into the current layer,\\ncreate new layers from the file, or map imported layers onto existing ones.\\nAfter import, Rayforge adds sensible default workflow steps -- a Contour step\\nfor vector layers and an Engrave step for layers with fills.\\n\\n## Lead-In / Lead-Out\\n\\nA new lead-in/lead-out postprocessor adds zero-power approach and exit moves\\nat the start and end of each contour. This helps the laser reach constant\\nvelocity before the actual cut begins, improving cut quality at entry and exit\\npoints.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- 3D model support for rotary axes (GLB format)\\n- Continuous laser mode and modal feedrate G-code options\\n- GRBL raster dialect with cleaner M4/M5 handling\\n- Grbl MKS DLC32 machine profile\\n- Material test: labels engraved first, overscan support, label speed setting\\n- Ctrl+F search in console and G-code viewer\\n- YUYV camera protocol support\\n- Addons can register toggles in the View menu\\n- Status bar removed, info moved to contextual locations\\n- Single instance lock\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.5\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-29-rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera.md","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools.","date":"2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.4","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-4"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"pdf","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/pdf"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sketcher"}],"readingTime":2.87,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.4","rotary","camera","pdf","sketcher"],"description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, direct\\nvector import for PDF files with layers, a guided camera calibration wizard,\\nand an improved sketcher with ellipse tools and smarter snapping.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Support\\n\\nYou can now engrave and cut cylindrical objects like tumblers, glasses, and\\npens. Rayforge wraps your design around the cylinder surface and shows a 3D\\npreview so you know exactly what the result will look like before you start.\\n\\nRotary mode can be toggled per layer, which means you can combine flat and\\ncylindrical work in a single project. A small rotary icon next to each layer\\nmakes it easy to see which layers will run on the rotary attachment.\\n\\nHead over to the [Rotary Setup](../docs/machine/rotary) page for details on\\nconfiguring your module.\\n\\n## PDF Import with Layers\\n\\nPDF files can now be imported as vector paths instead of being rasterized\\nfirst. This means cleaner lines, no quality loss, and \u2014 if the PDF contains\\nlayers \u2014 you can pick which layers to import, just like with SVG files.\\n\\nThis is especially handy when someone sends you a PDF that was exported from\\nIllustrator or Inkscape and you need clean cutting paths without re-drawing\\nanything.\\n\\n## Camera Calibration Wizard\\n\\nGetting a camera aligned to your laser bed just got easier. The new guided\\ncalibration wizard walks you through the process step by step using a printed\\ncalibration card. Rayforge computes a full distortion model from the card\\nimages, correcting for barrel distortion and perspective errors automatically.\\n\\nThe result is noticeably better alignment accuracy, especially with wide-angle\\nlenses or cameras mounted at an angle.\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe circle tool has been replaced with a more general **ellipse tool** that\\nhandles both circles and ellipses. The equality constraint now works on\\nellipses too.\\n\\nDrawing geometry also feels smoother now: many tools automatically apply\\nconstraints as you create shapes, and a new **magnetic snap** system replaces\\nthe old snap-to-grid behavior. Instead of locking to a fixed grid, magnetic\\nsnap pulls your cursor toward nearby geometry \u2014 points, lines, and endpoints \u2014\\nmaking it much easier to connect shapes precisely.\\n\\n## Better Framing Controls\\n\\nThe framing feature has new settings for finer control:\\n\\n- **Frame speed** is now configured per laser head\\n- **Corner dwell time** lets the laser pause briefly at each corner so you can\\n  see exactly where the boundary is\\n- **Repeat count** traces the outline multiple times for better visibility\\n\\n## Merge Lines Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor called **Merge Lines** detects overlapping path segments\\nand merges them into a single pass. This is useful when you import designs\\nwhere shapes share edges \u2014 think grid patterns or tessellations \u2014 and you want\\nto avoid cutting the same line twice.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- Machine profile for the Acmer S1 has been added\\n- G-code dialects are now independent copies, so customizing one never affects\\n  others\\n- Dialects support a separate laser-on command for focusing\\n- Large images are handled more safely to prevent running out of memory\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\n- Fixed material test producer issues\\n- Fixed position reporting for machines with only X and Y axes\\n- Fixed a sketcher issue where distance constraints could shadow the line\\n  underneath\\n- Fixed memory exhaustion when importing very large images\\n- Fixed a race condition during worker initialization\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.4\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-23-rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon.md","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on.","date":"2026-03-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.3","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-3"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/sketcher"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/addons"}],"readingTime":2.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.3","sketcher","bezier","addons"],"description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.3 brings bezier curve support to the parametric sketcher, a new\\nunified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to\\nan optional add-on.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Bezier Curves in the Sketcher\\n\\nThe headline feature for this release is full support for bezier curves in\\nthe parametric sketcher. The old line tool has been replaced with a new\\nunified **path tool** that seamlessly combines lines and curves.\\n\\nYou can now:\\n\\n- Draw smooth bezier curves with intuitive handle-based editing\\n- Connect curves to existing geometry - the path edit tool can snap to\\n  existing points in your sketch\\n- Make endpoints smooth or symmetric when they\'re connected by a coincident\\n  constraint - perfect for creating seamless curves\\n- Convert bezier curves back to straight lines with the new \\"straighten\\"\\n  tool\\n\\nThis has been one of the most requested features, and we\'re excited to see\\nwhat you create with it.\\n\\n## Sketcher is Now an Add-on\\n\\nContinuing the modularization work from version 1.2, the sketcher has been\\nmoved to an add-on. It\'s installed and enabled by default, so existing users\\nwon\'t notice any difference. But if you prefer a minimal setup without\\nparametric sketching, you can now disable it.\\n\\nThis change also comes with new extension registries that make it easier for\\nadd-on developers to extend Rayforge.\\n\\n## Sketcher Quality-of-Life Improvements\\n\\nThe sketcher received several smaller but impactful improvements:\\n\\n**Grid Tool**\\nA new tool to toggle grid visibility for better alignment.\\n\\n**Conflicting Constraints**\\nWhen constraints conflict with each other, they\'re now highlighted in the\\npanel so you can quickly identify and fix the problem.\\n\\n**Show/Hide Controls**\\nNew toggle buttons let you show or hide construction geometry and constraints\\nindividually.\\n\\n**Shift Constrains Movement**\\nHold Shift while dragging to constrain movement to the nearest axis - great\\nfor keeping things aligned.\\n\\n**Cleaner Background**\\nThe gray background area is now hidden for a cleaner editing experience.\\n\\n## More Efficient G-code\\n\\nRayforge now produces more compact G-code by omitting unchanged coordinates.\\nIf you\'re cutting along the X-axis, for example, only the X coordinate will\\nbe emitted on each line. This makes files smaller and cleaner, and makes\\nthe old \\"no-Z\\" dialect variants obsolete (they\'ve been removed).\\n\\nThe G-code viewer also got some updates:\\n\\n- Shows line count and byte size\\n- Always displays at least the first 20,000 lines\\n\\n## Raster Operation Enhancements\\n\\nNew settings for sample interval and power levels give you more control over\\nyour raster operations. These are particularly useful for fine-tuning results\\non materials that need precise power management.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- All icons normalized to 32x32 viewbox for consistent appearance\\n- AI workpiece generator now creates sketches when the geometry can be mapped\\n- Updated translations\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release fixes many issues:\\n\\n- Fixed fillet and chamfer tools not working correctly\\n- Fixed texture encoder drawing spaced dots instead of lines in some cases\\n- Fixed G1 being emitted without coordinates when all coordinates were unchanged\\n- Fixed loading project files with unknown assets\\n- Fixed issues when disabling and re-enabling add-ons at runtime\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.3\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-10-rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai.md","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows.","date":"2026-03-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.2","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/addons"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"ai","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/ai"}],"readingTime":3.36,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.2","addons","camera","ai"],"description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.2 brings an AI workpiece generator, significant camera\\nenhancements, and a completely revamped add-on system with core\\nfunctionality now available as optional modules.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## AI Workpiece Generator Add-on\\n\\nA new experimental add-on allows generating workpieces from text prompts.\\nThis is great for quickly creating simple designs or getting inspiration\\nfor new projects.\\n\\nThis is a first step, and we\'re excited about the possibilities this\\nopens up for the future!\\n\\n## Camera Enhancements\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of **MausRundung**, the camera system has\\nreceived a major overhaul:\\n\\n### Image Enhancement\\n\\n- Temporal noise reduction with configurable strength\\n- Cleaner preview images, especially in low-light conditions\\n\\n### Fisheye Distortion Correction\\n\\n- Radial distortion correction (k1, k2 parameters)\\n- Tangential distortion correction (p1, p2 parameters)\\n- Perfect for wide-angle lenses\\n\\n### Improved Alignment UI\\n\\n- Zoom, pan, and keyboard navigation in the alignment dialog\\n- Better point dragging with visual feedback\\n- Image stretching and positioning controls with offsets\\n\\n## Improved Add-on System\\n\\nThe add-on system has been greatly improved. The main change is that much\\nof the core functionality has been moved into add-ons that are installed\\nby default, but can be disabled or enabled as needed:\\n\\n**Core as Add-ons**\\nThe built-in transformers and laser essentials have been converted to\\nadd-ons. This makes Rayforge more modular - you can disable features you\\ndon\'t need or enable only what you want.\\n\\n**Add-on Capabilities**\\nAdd-ons can now:\\n- Register transformers (post-processors) for custom G-code manipulation\\n- Register keyboard shortcuts for custom workflows\\n- Hook into the backend and frontend independently\\n\\n**Commercial Support**\\nThe system now supports paid and third-party add-ons, enabling developers\\nto create commercial extensions for Rayforge.\\n\\n## Stock Improvements\\n\\nStock handling is now more flexible:\\n\\n- **Document-level stock** - stock is no longer tied to individual layers\\n- **Duplicate stock** using Ctrl+D\\n- **Non-rectangular stock** - convert any workpiece to stock for irregular\\n  materials\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe parametric sketcher received several quality-of-life improvements in\\nthis release:\\n\\n- **Live preview for line tool** - see the line before you commit\\n- **Dimension display** - shows dimensions while adding geometry\\n- **Snap-to-grid** - hold Ctrl to snap to the grid\\n- **Entity highlighting** - hovered entities and constraints are highlighted\\n- **Toolbar shortcuts** - shows currently available keyboard shortcuts\\n- **Connected selection** - Shift+Double click selects connected geometry\\n- **Arc radius adjustment** - change arc radius while adding the second endpoint\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Crop to Stock Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor that automatically crops operations to your stock\\nboundaries, saving time and material.\\n\\n### Inter-Workpiece Path Optimization\\n\\nThe path optimizer now also optimizes the workpiece order, reducing travel\\ndistance when working with multiple workpieces in a single job. Previously,\\nRayforge only optimized travel paths within individual workpieces.\\n\\n### Configurable Cut/Raster Colors\\n\\nEach laser can now have its own cut and raster colors, making it easier\\nto distinguish between different laser heads.\\n\\n### Quick WCS Positioning\\n\\nClick anywhere on the canvas to set the work coordinate system origin.\\n\\n### OMTech K40+ Profile\\n\\nNew machine profile for the popular OMTech K40+ laser cutter.\\n\\n### Mach4 G-code Dialect\\n\\nNew built-in G-code dialect for Mach4 controllers using M67 for spindle\\nspeed (laser power) control.\\n\\n### Platform Updates\\n\\n- Updated macOS support thanks to **Pablo Gil**\\n- Flatpak updates thanks to **fllmn**\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Add-on not enabled immediately after installation\\n- macOS bundle issues with GTK modules and built-in add-ons\\n- Tasker startup crash with DictProxy type annotations\\n- Old project files not showing new transformers\\n- SVG exporter stacking multiple workpieces on top of each other\\n- Auto layout for rotated stock\\n- Windows build using wrong version string on forks\\n- Mac and Windows builds not finding icon\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n- froqstar\\n\\nAnd thanks to **MausRundung** for the camera enhancements, **Pablo Gil** for\\nmacOS updates, and **fllmn** for Flatpak updates!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.2\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-27-rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite.md","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance.","date":"2026-02-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.1","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"pipeline","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/pipeline"},{"inline":true,"label":"raster","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/raster"},{"inline":true,"label":"gcode","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/gcode"}],"readingTime":2.48,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.1","pipeline","raster","gcode"],"description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Uma Celebra\xe7\xe3o do Primeiro Anivers\xe1rio","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.1](/images/rayforge-1.1.png)\\n\\nRayforge 1.1 brings a powerful new G-code console, unified raster operations,\\nand a completely rebuilt data pipeline for improved performance and stability.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## MacOS Support\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of GitHub user **pgilfernandez**, Rayforge\\nnow officially supports macOS! Both Intel and Apple Silicon Macs are\\nsupported. This has been a long-requested feature, and we\'re thrilled to\\nwelcome Mac users to the Rayforge community.\\n\\n## The Big Story: Complete Pipeline Rewrite\\n\\nThe headline feature of this release is a complete rewrite of the data\\npipeline backend. The new architecture is based on a Directed Acyclic Graph\\n(DAG), which brings significant improvements:\\n\\n- **Better performance** for complex projects with many operations\\n- **Reduced memory usage** through more efficient data handling\\n- **Smoother UI responsiveness** during heavy processing\\n- **Fixed memory leaks** that affected long editing sessions\\n\\nThis foundational upgrade makes Rayforge more robust and prepares the\\ncodebase for future features.\\n\\n## Unified Raster Operations\\n\\nThe old \\"raster\\", \\"depth\\", and \\"dither\\" operations have been merged into a\\nsingle, unified raster operation. This simplifies the workflow while giving\\nyou more control:\\n\\n- **Configurable line distance** in all raster operations\\n- **New \\"Raster (Dither)\\" operation** with configurable algorithms\\n- **Auto thresholding** for Variable Power and Multipass modes\\n- **Histogram** in the raster engraver for visual threshold setting\\n- **Symbolic visualization** of raster direction in the rasterizer\\n\\n## G-code Console\\n\\nThe log view has been replaced with a fully-featured G-code terminal. You can\\nnow send commands directly to your machine, view responses in real-time, and\\ninteract with your laser cutter more directly than ever before.\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Export Support\\n\\nYou can now export your documents or selected objects to SVG and DXF formats.\\nThis is great for sharing designs or using them in other software.\\n\\n### Sketcher Improvements\\n\\n- **Angle constraints** are now available in the parametric sketcher\\n- **Conflicting constraints** are highlighted in red for easier debugging\\n\\n### Machine Configuration\\n\\n- Axis extents, work surface, and soft limits can now be configured per machine\\n- Built-in G-code dialect supporting dynamic power mode\\n\\n### Other Additions\\n\\n- Increased maximum laser spot size to 10 mm\\n- `RAYFORGE_MAX_WORKERS` environment variable to limit processes\\n- macOS packaging scripts and resources for better platform support\\n- `--uiscript` CLI argument for executing scripts after the UI is up\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Multiple memory leaks in the data pipeline\\n- Race conditions between worker pool task completion and pipeline shutdown\\n- Camera device scanning crash on Windows\\n- Multipass post-processor exception\\n- Rasterizer angle causing distortion\\n- Various macOS issues: shm_open length errors, SVG rendering fallback,\\n  keyboard shortcuts\\n- Workpiece stage not emitting correct node state\\n- Zoom resolution stuck until resizing at least once\\n- Blurry view overlay on startup\\n- Unresponsive serial ports now handled gracefully\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n\\nThank you for supporting Rayforge development!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.1\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","source":"@site/i18n/pt-BR/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026-01-29-rayforge-1.0-first-birthday.md","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Uma Celebra\xe7\xe3o do Primeiro Anivers\xe1rio","description":"Rayforge 1.0","date":"2026-01-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/1"},{"inline":true,"label":"milestone","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/milestone"}],"readingTime":3.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Uma Celebra\xe7\xe3o do Primeiro Anivers\xe1rio","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1","milestone"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"},"nextItem":{"title":"5 Dicas para Melhores Resultados de Grava\xe7\xe3o a Laser com Rayforge","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.0](/images/rayforge-1.0.png)\\n\\nHoje marca um marco especial para o Rayforge - estamos lan\xe7ando a vers\xe3o\\n1.0 exatamente no primeiro anivers\xe1rio do projeto! O que come\xe7ou como um\\n\xfanico commit em 1\xba de fevereiro de 2025 cresceu para uma plataforma completa\\nde corte e grava\xe7\xe3o a laser.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## A Jornada At\xe9 Aqui\\n\\nDurante o \xfaltimo ano, o Rayforge evoluiu de uma ferramenta b\xe1sica de\\ncontrole a laser para uma plataforma abrangente de design e manufatura.\\nConstru\xedmos tudo do zero: um sistema CAD 2D param\xe9trico, visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D\\nde G-code, suporte multicamadas, suporte multi-laser, alinhamento por\\nc\xe2mera, sistemas de coordenadas de trabalho, e muito mais.\\n\\nEste lan\xe7amento representa a culmina\xe7\xe3o dessa vis\xe3o - uma ferramenta\\nest\xe1vel e pronta para produ\xe7\xe3o que pode lidar com fluxos de trabalho reais\\nde corte e grava\xe7\xe3o a laser.\\n\\n## O que h\xe1 de Novo no 1.0\\n\\n### Salvar/Carregar Projetos\\n\\nO recurso mais solicitado finalmente chegou. Agora voc\xea pode salvar seus\\nfluxos de trabalho completos e restaur\xe1-los posteriormente. As extens\xf5es\\nde arquivo `.ryp` (projeto) e `.rfs` (esbo\xe7o) s\xe3o registradas em todo o\\nsistema, ent\xe3o voc\xea pode clicar duas vezes em seus projetos para abri-los\\ndiretamente. Um menu de arquivos recentes fornece acesso r\xe1pido ao seu\\ntrabalho.\\n\\n### Esbo\xe7ador Param\xe9trico com Suporte a Texto\\n\\nO esbo\xe7ador agora suporta texto com integra\xe7\xe3o completa de restri\xe7\xf5es.\\nAdicione texto aos seus esbo\xe7os, aplique restri\xe7\xf5es de propor\xe7\xe3o, e\\ncontrole posicionamento e dimensionamento parametricamente. Isso abre um\\nmundo totalmente novo de possibilidades de design para placas gravadas a\\nlaser, r\xf3tulos e elementos decorativos.\\n\\n### Painel Inferior Unificado\\n\\nO di\xe1logo de jog e a visualiza\xe7\xe3o de log foram mesclados em um \xfanico\\npainel inferior unificado. Essa consolida\xe7\xe3o fornece um espa\xe7o de trabalho\\nmais limpo enquanto mant\xe9m ferramentas essenciais de controle e monitoramento\\nda m\xe1quina prontamente acess\xedveis. O painel apresenta acesso com abas aos\\ncontroles de jog e sa\xedda de log, facilitando a altern\xe2ncia entre opera\xe7\xf5es\\nsem perder espa\xe7o na tela.\\n\\n### Outras Melhorias\\n\\n- **Painel inferior**: O di\xe1logo de jog e visualiza\xe7\xe3o de log agora est\xe3o\\n  mesclados em um painel inferior unificado\\n- **Di\xe1logo de importa\xe7\xe3o**: Erros agora s\xe3o coletados e exibidos juntos\\n- **Importadores**: Quase completamente reescritos para melhor testabilidade\\n- **Estabilidade do esbo\xe7ador**: O solver agora direciona pontos para\\n  arrastar mais est\xe1vel\\n- **Corre\xe7\xf5es de bugs**: Importa\xe7\xe3o DXF multicamadas, bugs de alinhamento,\\n  problemas de centraliza\xe7\xe3o, e mais\\n\\n## Destaques de Recursos\\n\\nO Rayforge 1.0 inclui mais de 60 recursos:\\n\\n**Ferramentas de Design**\\n\\n- CAD 2D com esbo\xe7o param\xe9trico\\n- Restri\xe7\xf5es geom\xe9tricas e dimensionais\\n- Suporte a texto em esbo\xe7os\\n- Suporte multicamadas\\n\\n**Manufatura**\\n\\n- Opera\xe7\xf5es 2.5D (contorno, raster, grava\xe7\xe3o em profundidade)\\n- Suporte multi-laser\\n- Sistemas de Coordenadas de Trabalho (G54-G59)\\n- Otimiza\xe7\xe3o e suaviza\xe7\xe3o de trajet\xf3rias\\n- Abas de fixa\xe7\xe3o com posicionamento autom\xe1tico\\n\\n**Importa\xe7\xe3o/Exporta\xe7\xe3o**\\n\\n- Suporte a arquivos SVG, DXF, PDF, JPEG, PNG, BMP, Ruida\\n- Rastreamento vetorial com m\xfaltiplos algoritmos\\n- Pr\xe9-processamento de imagem (redu\xe7\xe3o de ru\xeddo, invers\xe3o, limiar)\\n\\n**Controle de M\xe1quina**\\n\\n- Perfis de m\xfaltiplas m\xe1quinas\\n- Configura\xe7\xf5es de firmware para GRBL, Smoothieware, Marlin\\n- Macros e ganchos de G-code\\n- Substitui\xe7\xe3o de vari\xe1veis\\n- Console de terminal com status em tempo real\\n\\n**Visualiza\xe7\xe3o**\\n\\n- Visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D de G-code com simula\xe7\xe3o completa\\n- Alinhamento por c\xe2mera\\n- Temas escuro e claro\\n- Suporte multil\xedngue\\n\\n## Um Olhar para Tr\xe1s\\n\\nO primeiro commit foi feito em 1\xba de fevereiro de 2025, \xe0s 19:37:27. Foi\\num simples \\"importa\xe7\xe3o inicial\\" com suporte b\xe1sico de renderiza\xe7\xe3o SVG.\\nDesde ent\xe3o, n\xf3s:\\n\\n- Lan\xe7amos 28 vers\xf5es (0.13 at\xe9 0.28, mais 1.0)\\n- Adicionamos mais de 60 recursos\\n- Corrigimos centenas de bugs\\n- Constru\xedmos uma comunidade de usu\xe1rios e colaboradores\\n- Criamos instaladores para Windows, Linux (deb, snap, flatpak) e macOS\\n\\n## O que Vem a Seguir?\\n\\nA vers\xe3o 1.0 \xe9 um marco, n\xe3o um destino. O roteiro \xe0 frente inclui:\\n\\n- Ferramentas vetoriais aprimoradas e capacidades de edi\xe7\xe3o\\n- Suporte mais amplo de hardware\\n- Otimiza\xe7\xf5es de desempenho para grandes projetos\\n- Mais perfis de m\xe1quina e dialetos\\n- Ecossistema de pacotes impulsionado pela comunidade\\n\\n## Baixe o Rayforge 1.0\\n\\nObtenha a vers\xe3o mais recente em nosso site: https://rayforge.org/\\n\\nInstaladores est\xe3o dispon\xedveis para:\\n\\n- Windows (instalador)\\n- Linux (deb, snap, flatpak)\\n- macOS (dmg)\\n\\n## Junte-se \xe0 Comunidade\\n\\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge\\n- **Discord**: https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ\\n- **Patreon**: https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap\\n\\nObrigado a todos que contribu\xedram, testaram, reportaram bugs, ou\\nsimplesmente usaram o Rayforge ao longo deste \xfaltimo ano. Aqui est\xe1 para\\noutro ano construindo o futuro da manufatura de c\xf3digo aberto!\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Feliz primeiro anivers\xe1rio, Rayforge! \ud83c\udf82*"},{"id":"5-tips-better-engraving","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/5-tips-better-engraving","source":"@site/i18n/pt-BR/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-02-20-5-tips-better-engraving.md","title":"5 Dicas para Melhores Resultados de Grava\xe7\xe3o a Laser com Rayforge","description":"Visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D","date":"2025-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"engraving","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/engraving"},{"inline":true,"label":"optimization","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/optimization"},{"inline":true,"label":"quality","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/quality"},{"inline":true,"label":"workflow","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/workflow"}],"readingTime":3.98,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"5-tips-better-engraving","title":"5 Dicas para Melhores Resultados de Grava\xe7\xe3o a Laser com Rayforge","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["engraving","optimization","quality","workflow"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Uma Celebra\xe7\xe3o do Primeiro Anivers\xe1rio","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"},"nextItem":{"title":"Suporte Multi-Laser - Escolha Diferentes Lasers para Cada Opera\xe7\xe3o","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![Visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D](/screenshots/main-3d.png)\\n\\nObter resultados de grava\xe7\xe3o a laser de qualidade profissional requer mais\\ndo que apenas bom hardware \u2014 suas configura\xe7\xf5es de software e fluxo de\\ntrabalho tamb\xe9m importam. Aqui est\xe3o cinco dicas para ajud\xe1-lo a aproveitar\\nao m\xe1ximo o Rayforge.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 1. Use Overscan para Grava\xe7\xe3o Raster mais Suave\\n\\nAo fazer grava\xe7\xe3o raster, um problema comum s\xe3o linhas vis\xedveis ou\\ninconsist\xeancias nas bordas onde o laser muda de dire\xe7\xe3o. Isso acontece\\nporque a cabe\xe7a do laser precisa desacelerar e acelerar, o que pode afetar\\na qualidade da grava\xe7\xe3o.\\n\\n**Solu\xe7\xe3o**: Habilite **Overscan** nas configura\xe7\xf5es da sua opera\xe7\xe3o raster.\\n\\nO overscan estende o trajeto de deslocamento do laser al\xe9m da \xe1rea de\\ngrava\xe7\xe3o real, permitindo que a cabe\xe7a atinja a velocidade m\xe1xima antes de\\nentrar na \xe1rea de trabalho e mantenha essa velocidade durante todo o\\npercurso. Isso resulta em uma grava\xe7\xe3o muito mais suave e consistente.\\n\\nPara habilitar o overscan:\\n\\n1. Selecione sua opera\xe7\xe3o raster\\n2. Abra as configura\xe7\xf5es da opera\xe7\xe3o\\n3. Habilite \\"Overscan\\" e defina a dist\xe2ncia (tipicamente 3-5mm funciona bem)\\n\\nSaiba mais em nosso [guia de Overscan](/docs/features/overscan).\\n\\n## 2. Otimize o Tempo de Deslocamento com Ordena\xe7\xe3o de Trajet\xf3rias\\n\\nPara opera\xe7\xf5es de contorno com muitos trajetos separados, a ordem em que\\no laser visita cada forma pode impactar significativamente o tempo total\\ndo trabalho.\\n\\n**Solu\xe7\xe3o**: Use a **otimiza\xe7\xe3o de tempo de deslocamento** integrada do\\nRayforge.\\n\\nO Rayforge pode reordenar automaticamente os trajetos para minimizar o\\ntempo de deslocamento sem corte. Isso \xe9 especialmente \xfatil para trabalhos\\ncom muitos objetos pequenos ou texto com m\xfaltiplas letras.\\n\\nA otimiza\xe7\xe3o de trajeto \xe9 tipicamente habilitada por padr\xe3o, mas voc\xea pode\\nverificar e ajust\xe1-la nas configura\xe7\xf5es da opera\xe7\xe3o de Contorno.\\n\\n## 3. Adicione Abas de Fixa\xe7\xe3o para Prevenir Movimento da Pe\xe7a\\n\\nNada \xe9 mais frustrante do que ter um trabalho de corte quase finalizado\\narruinado porque a pe\xe7a deslocou ou caiu atrav\xe9s da mesa da m\xe1quina no\\n\xfaltimo momento.\\n\\n**Solu\xe7\xe3o**: Use **Abas de Fixa\xe7\xe3o** para manter as pe\xe7as no lugar at\xe9 que\\no trabalho seja conclu\xeddo.\\n\\nAs abas de fixa\xe7\xe3o s\xe3o pequenas se\xe7\xf5es n\xe3o cortadas que mant\xeam sua pe\xe7a\\nconectada ao material circundante. Ap\xf3s a conclus\xe3o do trabalho, voc\xea pode\\nfacilmente remover a pe\xe7a e limpar as abas com uma faca ou lixa.\\n\\nO Rayforge suporta coloca\xe7\xe3o de abas tanto manual quanto autom\xe1tica:\\n\\n- **Manual**: Clique exatamente onde voc\xea quer as abas na tela\\n- **Autom\xe1tica**: Especifique o n\xfamero de abas e deixe o Rayforge\\n  distribu\xed-las uniformemente\\n\\nConfira a [documenta\xe7\xe3o de Abas de Fixa\xe7\xe3o](/docs/features/holding-tabs)\\npara um guia completo.\\n\\n## 4. Visualize Seu Trabalho em 3D Antes de Executar\\n\\nUm dos recursos mais valiosos do Rayforge \xe9 a visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D de G-code.\\n\xc9 tentador pular esta etapa e enviar o trabalho diretamente para a m\xe1quina,\\nmas reservar um momento para visualizar pode economizar tempo e materiais.\\n\\n**O que procurar na visualiza\xe7\xe3o**:\\n\\n- Verifique se todas as opera\xe7\xf5es est\xe3o sendo executadas na ordem correta\\n- Procure por quaisquer trajetos inesperados ou sobreposi\xe7\xf5es\\n- Confirme se opera\xe7\xf5es de m\xfaltiplas passagens t\xeam o n\xfamero correto de\\n  passagens\\n- Certifique-se de que os limites do trabalho se encaixam dentro do seu\\n  material\\n\\nPara abrir a visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D, clique no bot\xe3o **Visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D** na barra\\nde ferramentas principal ap\xf3s gerar seu G-code.\\n\\nSaiba mais sobre a visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D em nossa\\n[documenta\xe7\xe3o de UI](/docs/ui/3d-preview).\\n\\n## 5. Use Ganchos de G-code Personalizados para Fluxos de Trabalho Consistentes\\n\\nSe voc\xea se encontra executando os mesmos comandos G-code antes ou depois\\nde cada trabalho \u2014 como homing, ligar um assistente de ar, ou executar uma\\nrotina de foco \u2014 voc\xea pode automatizar isso com **Macros e Ganchos de\\nG-code**.\\n\\n**Casos de uso comuns**:\\n\\n- **Gancho pr\xe9-trabalho**: Leva a m\xe1quina \xe0 origem, liga assistente de ar,\\n  executa uma rotina de auto-foco\\n- **Gancho p\xf3s-trabalho**: Desliga assistente de ar, retorna \xe0 posi\xe7\xe3o de\\n  origem, toca um som de conclus\xe3o\\n- **Macros espec\xedficas por camada**: Muda a altura do foco entre opera\xe7\xf5es,\\n  troca m\xf3dulos de laser\\n\\nOs ganchos suportam substitui\xe7\xe3o de vari\xe1veis, ent\xe3o voc\xea pode referenciar\\npropriedades do trabalho como espessura do material, tipo de opera\xe7\xe3o, e\\nmais.\\n\\nExemplo de gancho pr\xe9-trabalho:\\n\\n```gcode\\nG28 ; Home all axes\\nM8 ; Turn on air assist\\nG0 Z{focus_height} ; Move to focus height\\n```\\n\\nConsulte nosso [guia de Macros e Ganchos de G-code](/docs/machine/hooks-macros)\\npara exemplos detalhados e refer\xeancia de vari\xe1veis.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Dica B\xf4nus: Teste em Material de Sobra Primeiro\\n\\nEmbora isso n\xe3o seja espec\xedfico do Rayforge, vale a pena repetir: sempre\\nteste novas configura\xe7\xf5es, opera\xe7\xf5es ou materiais em sobra primeiro. Use\\nos perfis de material e predefini\xe7\xf5es de opera\xe7\xe3o do Rayforge para salvar\\nsuas configura\xe7\xf5es testadas para uso futuro.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Tem suas pr\xf3prias dicas e truques do Rayforge? Compartilhe com a comunidade\\nnas [Discuss\xf5es do GitHub](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/discussions)!*"},{"id":"multi-laser-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/multi-laser-support","source":"@site/i18n/pt-BR/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-01-10-multi-laser-support.md","title":"Suporte Multi-Laser - Escolha Diferentes Lasers para Cada Opera\xe7\xe3o","description":"Um dos recursos mais poderosos no Rayforge \xe9 a capacidade de atribuir","date":"2025-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"multi-laser","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/multi-laser"},{"inline":true,"label":"operations","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/operations"},{"inline":true,"label":"workflow","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/workflow"}],"readingTime":2.77,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"multi-laser-support","title":"Suporte Multi-Laser - Escolha Diferentes Lasers para Cada Opera\xe7\xe3o","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["multi-laser","operations","workflow"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"5 Dicas para Melhores Resultados de Grava\xe7\xe3o a Laser com Rayforge","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bem-vindo ao Rayforge: Software Moderno de Controle a Laser","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/welcome-to-rayforge"}},"content":"Um dos recursos mais poderosos no Rayforge \xe9 a capacidade de atribuir\\ndiferentes lasers a diferentes opera\xe7\xf5es dentro de um \xfanico trabalho. Isso\\nabre possibilidades emocionantes para configura\xe7\xf5es multi-ferramentas e\\nfluxos de trabalho especializados.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## O que \xe9 Suporte Multi-Laser?\\n\\nSe sua m\xe1quina est\xe1 equipada com m\xfaltiplos m\xf3dulos de laser \u2014 digamos, um\\nlaser de diodo para grava\xe7\xe3o e um laser CO2 para corte, ou lasers de diodo\\nde diferentes pot\xeancias otimizados para diferentes materiais \u2014 o Rayforge\\npermite aproveitar ao m\xe1ximo essa configura\xe7\xe3o.\\n\\nCom suporte multi-laser, voc\xea pode:\\n\\n- **Atribuir diferentes lasers a diferentes opera\xe7\xf5es** em seu trabalho\\n- **Alternar entre m\xf3dulos de laser** automaticamente durante a execu\xe7\xe3o\\n  do trabalho\\n- **Otimizar para material e tarefa** usando a ferramenta certa para cada\\n  opera\xe7\xe3o\\n\\n## Casos de Uso\\n\\n### Grava\xe7\xe3o e Corte H\xedbrido\\n\\nImagine que voc\xea est\xe1 trabalhando em um projeto de placa de madeira:\\n\\n1. **Opera\xe7\xe3o 1**: Use um laser de diodo de baixa pot\xeancia para gravar\\n   texto fino e gr\xe1ficos detalhados\\n2. **Opera\xe7\xe3o 2**: Mude para um laser CO2 de maior pot\xeancia para cortar\\n   o formato da placa\\n\\nCom o Rayforge, voc\xea simplesmente atribui cada opera\xe7\xe3o ao laser apropriado\\nem seu perfil de m\xe1quina, e o software cuida do resto.\\n\\n### Otimiza\xe7\xe3o Espec\xedfica por Material\\n\\nDiferentes tipos de laser se destacam em diferentes materiais:\\n\\n- **Lasers de diodo**: \xd3timos para grava\xe7\xe3o em madeira, couro e alguns\\n  pl\xe1sticos\\n- **Lasers CO2**: Excelentes para cortar acr\xedlico, madeira e outros\\n  materiais org\xe2nicos\\n- **Lasers de fibra**: Perfeitos para marcar metais\\n\\nSe voc\xea tem m\xfaltiplos tipos de laser em um sistema de p\xf3rtico, o suporte\\nmulti-laser do Rayforge permite usar a ferramenta ideal para cada parte do\\nseu projeto.\\n\\n## Como Configurar\\n\\n### 1. Configure M\xfaltiplos Lasers em Seu Perfil de M\xe1quina\\n\\nV\xe1 em **Configura\xe7\xe3o da M\xe1quina \u2192 M\xfaltiplos Lasers** e defina cada m\xf3dulo\\nde laser em seu sistema. Voc\xea pode especificar:\\n\\n- Tipo de laser e faixa de pot\xeancia\\n- Posi\xe7\xf5es de deslocamento (se os lasers est\xe3o montados em locais diferentes)\\n- Compatibilidade com materiais\\n\\nConsulte nosso [Guia de Configura\xe7\xe3o de Laser](/docs/machine/laser)\\npara instru\xe7\xf5es detalhadas.\\n\\n### 2. Atribua Lasers \xe0s Opera\xe7\xf5es\\n\\nAo criar opera\xe7\xf5es em seu projeto:\\n\\n1. Selecione a opera\xe7\xe3o (Contorno, Raster, etc.)\\n2. Nas configura\xe7\xf5es da opera\xe7\xe3o, escolha qual laser usar no menu suspenso\\n3. Configure os par\xe2metros da opera\xe7\xe3o espec\xedficos para aquele laser\\n\\n### 3. Visualize e Execute\\n\\nUse a visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D para verificar suas trajet\xf3rias de ferramenta, depois\\nenvie o trabalho para sua m\xe1quina. O Rayforge gerar\xe1 automaticamente os\\ncomandos G-code apropriados para alternar entre lasers conforme necess\xe1rio.\\n\\n## Detalhes T\xe9cnicos\\n\\nNos bastidores, o Rayforge usa comandos G-code para alternar entre m\xf3dulos\\nde laser. A implementa\xe7\xe3o exata depende do seu firmware e configura\xe7\xe3o de\\nhardware, mas abordagens comuns incluem:\\n\\n- **M3/M4 com deslocamentos de ferramenta**: Alterna entre lasers usando\\n  comandos de troca de ferramenta\\n- **Controle GPIO**: Usa pinos GPIO suportados pelo firmware para\\n  habilitar/desabilitar diferentes m\xf3dulos de laser\\n- **Macros personalizados**: Define macros pr\xe9 e p\xf3s-opera\xe7\xe3o para troca\\n  de laser\\n\\n## Come\xe7ando\\n\\nO suporte multi-laser est\xe1 dispon\xedvel no Rayforge 0.15 e posterior. Para\\ncome\xe7ar:\\n\\n1. Atualize para a vers\xe3o mais recente\\n2. Configure seu perfil de m\xe1quina com m\xfaltiplos lasers\\n3. Experimente em um projeto de teste!\\n\\nConfira a [documenta\xe7\xe3o de Perfis de M\xe1quina](/docs/machine/general)\\npara mais detalhes.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Tem uma configura\xe7\xe3o multi-laser? Adorar\xedamos ouvir sobre sua experi\xeancia!\\nCompartilhe seus projetos e feedback no\\n[GitHub](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge).*"},{"id":"welcome-to-rayforge","metadata":{"permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/welcome-to-rayforge","source":"@site/i18n/pt-BR/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024-12-15-welcome-to-rayforge.md","title":"Bem-vindo ao Rayforge: Software Moderno de Controle a Laser","description":"Janela Principal do Rayforge","date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"introduction","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/introduction"},{"inline":true,"label":"features","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/tags/features"}],"readingTime":1.98,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/pt-BR/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-to-rayforge","title":"Bem-vindo ao Rayforge: Software Moderno de Controle a Laser","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["introduction","features"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Suporte Multi-Laser - Escolha Diferentes Lasers para Cada Opera\xe7\xe3o","permalink":"/pt-BR/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![Janela Principal do Rayforge](/screenshots/main-standard.png)\\n\\nEstamos entusiasmados em apresentar o Rayforge, um enviador de G-code moderno\\ne software de controle de c\xf3digo aberto, projetado especificamente para\\ncortadoras e gravadoras a laser baseadas em GRBL.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Por que o Rayforge?\\n\\nNo mundo de corte e grava\xe7\xe3o a laser, ter um software confi\xe1vel e intuitivo\\n\xe9 t\xe3o importante quanto ter hardware de qualidade. O Rayforge foi constru\xeddo\\ndo zero com foco em:\\n\\n- **Experi\xeancia do Usu\xe1rio Moderna**: Constru\xeddo com Gtk4 e Libadwaita, o\\n  Rayforge oferece uma interface limpa e nativa que se sente em casa no\\n  Linux e Windows\\n- **Recursos Profissionais**: Fluxos de trabalho multicamadas, visualiza\xe7\xe3o\\n  3D, integra\xe7\xe3o com c\xe2mera e gera\xe7\xe3o avan\xe7ada de trajet\xf3rias\\n- **Flexibilidade**: Suporte para m\xfaltiplos perfis de m\xe1quina, macros\\n  personalizados e amplas op\xe7\xf5es de configura\xe7\xe3o\\n- **Desenvolvimento Aberto**: Impulsionado pela comunidade com contribui\xe7\xf5es\\n  bem-vindas\\n\\n## O que Torna o Rayforge Diferente?\\n\\n### Opera\xe7\xf5es Multicamadas\\n\\nUm dos recursos de destaque do Rayforge \xe9 seu fluxo de trabalho multicamadas.\\nAtribua opera\xe7\xf5es diferentes a camadas diferentes em seu design \u2014 grave\\ndetalhes finos em uma camada, depois corte a pe\xe7a em outra. Tudo gerenciado\\nde forma integrada em uma \xfanica interface.\\n\\n### Visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D de G-code\\n\\nAntes de enviar seu trabalho para a m\xe1quina, visualize exatamente o que\\nacontecer\xe1 com nossa visualiza\xe7\xe3o 3D de G-code. Detecte problemas potenciais\\nantes que eles ocorram e economize tempo e materiais.\\n\\n### Integra\xe7\xe3o com C\xe2mera\\n\\nUse uma c\xe2mera USB para alinhamento preciso da pe\xe7a de trabalho,\\nposicionamento e at\xe9 rastreamento de fundo. Perfeito para posicionar designs\\nem materiais pr\xe9-existentes ou criar gabaritos.\\n\\n### Gera\xe7\xe3o Avan\xe7ada de Trajet\xf3rias\\n\\nO Rayforge inclui rastreamento de imagem de alta qualidade, otimiza\xe7\xe3o de\\ntempo de deslocamento, suaviza\xe7\xe3o de trajet\xf3ria e interpola\xe7\xe3o de tamanho\\nde ponto para garantir que seus projetos saiam exatamente como planejados.\\n\\n## Come\xe7ando\\n\\nPronto para experimentar o Rayforge? Confira nosso\\n[Guia de Instala\xe7\xe3o](/docs/getting-started/installation) para come\xe7ar.\\nSeja voc\xea est\xe1 usando Ubuntu, outra distribui\xe7\xe3o Linux via Snap, ou Windows,\\nn\xf3s cobrimos voc\xea.\\n\\n## Junte-se \xe0 Comunidade\\n\\nO Rayforge \xe9 de c\xf3digo aberto e impulsionado pela comunidade. Agradecemos\\ncontribui\xe7\xf5es de todos os tipos:\\n\\n- Reporte bugs e solicite recursos no\\n  [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/issues)\\n- Contribua com c\xf3digo via\\n  [pull requests](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/pulls)\\n- Melhore a documenta\xe7\xe3o\\n- Compartilhe seus projetos e experi\xeancias\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Tem perguntas ou feedback? Junte-se \xe0 conversa no GitHub ou confira\\nnossa [documenta\xe7\xe3o](/docs/getting-started/installation).*"}]}}')}}]);